{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3029450,"name":"Jacob ","username":"Muskmelon","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/e5b9ba/{size}.png","created_at":"2022-03-24T14:25:37.430Z","cooked":"<p>We have encountered a strange problem when running our robot. We will run a motor on the robot and it will continue running after we stop giving it input. If the robot is disabled the motor stops but when enabled again it continues this behavior. The only way to stopp it is by power cycling. We don‚Äôt believe it to be joystick drift as it has happened with robot systems that run autonomously and inputs that use buttons. We have seen it happen with falcon 500 motors and cim motors ran off a talon SRX with a ubob to a through boar hex Encoder. We appear to maintain coms throughout the occurrence. This also seems to happen randomly as far as we can tell, it hasn‚Äôt happened enough times to determine a pattern. Has anyone encountered a similar problem. We are trying to determine if the problem is hardware or software. I personally don‚Äôt believe it to be hardware because in past experiences bad hardware brakes things less subtley.</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2022-03-24T14:25:37.430Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":26,"reads":129,"readers_count":128,"score":155.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":406720,"topic_slug":"robot-continues-to-move-after-input-is-stoped","display_username":"Jacob ","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":52117,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Electrical"},"post_url":"/t/robot-continues-to-move-after-input-is-stoped/406720/1","custom_user_title":"Electrical","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3029451,"name":"Ash Dorsey","username":"frog","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/frog/{size}/160612_2.png","created_at":"2022-03-24T14:27:54.202Z","cooked":"<p>Have you checked your controllers with <a href="https://gamepad-tester.com/" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">https://gamepad-tester.com/</a> ? You did say it happens on auto so that is strange.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2022-03-24T14:27:54.202Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":127,"readers_count":126,"score":25.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":406720,"topic_slug":"robot-continues-to-move-after-input-is-stoped","display_username":"Ash Dorsey","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://gamepad-tester.com/","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Gamepad Tester","clicks":6}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":45353,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/robot-continues-to-move-after-input-is-stoped/406720/2","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3029457,"name":"NewtonCrosby","username":"NewtonCrosby","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/n/ed8c4c/{size}.png","created_at":"2022-03-24T14:38:54.110Z","cooked":"<p>Nearly a 100% likelihood it‚Äôs software.<br>
Does the problem persist if you merely restart the robot code, rather than fully power cycle the robot?</p>
<p>Putting your code on github may help us figure out the software issues.  Diagnosing the software issue become more difficult without context, timebased, command-based, programming language, etc.</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2022-03-24T14:38:54.110Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":117,"readers_count":116,"score":43.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":406720,"topic_slug":"robot-continues-to-move-after-input-is-stoped","display_username":"NewtonCrosby","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":31346,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/robot-continues-to-move-after-input-is-stoped/406720/3","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3029460,"name":"Jacob ","username":"Muskmelon","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/e5b9ba/{size}.png","created_at":"2022-03-24T14:41:47.292Z","cooked":"<p>Yes thats what I think as well though I‚Äôm the electrical guy so I might be a bit biased. I‚Äôll see if I can get the programming guys to post there stuff.</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2022-03-24T14:41:47.292Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":108,"readers_count":107,"score":26.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":406720,"topic_slug":"robot-continues-to-move-after-input-is-stoped","display_username":"Jacob ","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":31346,"username":"NewtonCrosby","name":"NewtonCrosby","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/n/ed8c4c/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":52117,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Electrical"},"post_url":"/t/robot-continues-to-move-after-input-is-stoped/406720/4","custom_user_title":"Electrical","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3029462,"name":"Joshua Epperson","username":"jepperson","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/74df32/{size}.png","created_at":"2022-03-24T14:47:50.881Z","cooked":"<p>Your coders probably did something like this in their drivetrain code in the periodic subsystem function</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">RobotContainer.differentialDrive.arcadeDrive(leftJoystick, rightJoystick);
</code></pre>
<p>they need to do something like this</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">if (Math.abs(leftJoystick) &gt; deadband || Math.abs(rightJoystick) &gt; deadband) {
RobotContainer.differentialDrive.arcadeDrive(leftJoystick, rightJoystick);
} else {
  RobotContainer.differentialDrive.arcadeDrive(0,0);
}
</code></pre>
<p>You might also want to put an override boolean if you also haven‚Äôt laid out your command project properly for autonomous commands</p>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2022-03-24T14:47:50.881Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":95,"readers_count":94,"score":34.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":406720,"topic_slug":"robot-continues-to-move-after-input-is-stoped","display_username":"Joshua Epperson","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":52117,"username":"Muskmelon","name":"Jacob ","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/e5b9ba/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":49514,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/robot-continues-to-move-after-input-is-stoped/406720/5","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3029487,"name":"","username":"FRC6302","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/frc6302/{size}/165591_2.png","created_at":"2022-03-24T15:31:59.624Z","cooked":"<p>Have you updated your WPILib/Rio to the lastest versions? This was a bug in a previous version I‚Äôm pretty sure</p>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2022-03-24T15:31:59.624Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":7,"reads":76,"readers_count